title.undefined: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Product Module

description.undefined: The Product module of CEON (Circular Economy Ontology Network).

coversRequirements.value: In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.1: CVN-Resource-2, CVN-ResrouceType-4, C11-2, C12-1, C13-3, E2-1, T8-3.

title.value: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Product Module

comment.undefined: Represents that something is compliant with some standard or has a received a certain certification.

comment.en: A constituent is a component of object.

comment.undefined: The generic relation representing the particpation of a resource in some relation. For example, it can be specialized to represent a reified version of an object or data property.
Represents the participation of objects in some situation.

comment.en: A product composition is the composed information of a product in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a matter.

comment.undefined: A digital object, e.g. a computer file, that is located on some server, hard drive, or on the web. Most often the digital object is the realization of some piece of information.

comment.en: A batch of objects is a collection of physical objects that are of the same type, e.g. a set of items (product objects) adhering to the same product model.
A product composition is the composed information of a product in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a product.

comment.undefined: The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a certain resource, e.g. an organisation or individual (actor) owning (role) a specific product (resource) at a specific point or period in time.

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a value network or a process in such a network, e.g. an organisation (actor) acting as the recycler (role) in a glass recycling value netowrk (network) at a specific point or period in time. Or an organisation (actor) acting as the dismantler (role) in a dismantling step of a building deconstruction process (process step) at a specific point or period in time.

comment.en: A set of objects is a set of physical objects (items) that can be of different types, i.e. different kinds of items.

comment.undefined: A product object composition is the composed information of a product object in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a product object.
Something that the actor is capable of doing, e.g. perfomring a certain role in a process, based on some properties, such as access to infrastructure, resources and know-how.

comment.en: A product object is a physical object put into a market for sale, i.e. corresponding to the notion of an item, which conforms to the abstract idea of a product model. The product can be a thing that grows naturally or produced through some chemical or manufacturing processes.
Information is an abstract concept that represents any kind of interpretations. For instance, information can be data generated by software systems or data used by people for communications.
Represents the common sense notion of a product, i.e. the abstract notion of a product type or product model, which is a model that is used for manufacturing products.

A composition is used to represent how a whole or mixture is made up. E.g., for chemical elements composing a chemical structure, the compostion should hold information of the ratio of the composing chemical elments.

comment.undefined: A collaboration between a set of actors.
The type of an actor, e.g. the type of company, or a specific subtype based on the organisations capabilities.

definition.value: A coherent set of direct positions in space. The positions are held within a Spatial Reference System (SRS).
A coherent set of direct positions in space. The positions are held within a Spatial Reference System (SRS).

comment.undefined: A role that an actor can take in a specific context. Applies both to roles in the context of resources, such as owner, manufacturer, reseller etc. of that resource, as well as roles in relation to a circular value network, such as recycler, dismantler, transporter etc., in relation to a material flow.

comment.en: A matter is a physical substance.
A resource able to be handled in the context of a circular value network, e.g. data generated by software systems in the CVN, materials or prooducts as physical objects handled in the CVN.
A physical object is a collection of matter.

comment.undefined: An agent able to act in the context of a circular value network, e.g. an organisation, person.
The type of the actor.
The point in time when something took place or was valid.
Used to represent the country of assembly of a product or product object
Used to represent the location of manufacture of a product or product object
Relates some properties to the capability, such as the parameters of it, or the needed resources.
The end of a time interval.
Relates to the actor holding the capability.
Participating object in a resource participation. This is part of a resource participation that can be a directional relation, and the participating object is the end point of the relation.

comment.en: batchSize intends to repsent how many physical objects are belong to a batch of objects.
hasMatter intends to represent that a physical object can have a collection of matter.

comment.undefined: Used to link something (e.g., product or process) to a compliance.
The resource that this participation relation relates to, i.e. for which the actor holds the specified role.

comment.en: associatedWithProductModel intends to represent the product model to which a product compopsition information regards to.

comment.undefined: Relates a thing, e.g. a digital object, or a physical object, to the information it is a realization of. C.f. a physical book that is the realization of a novel, or a pdf or Excel-file that is a realization of a certain data sheet.
